      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a mechanically sound example of the legendary S54-powered platform. The 3.2L naturally aspirated straight-six features six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure double-VANOS system, both recently serviced to ensure precise cam timing and throttle response. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a tactile 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and a factory variable M differential lock. Crucially, the rear subframe has been reinforced with structural plates, addressing the chassis's primary weak point. The suspension geometry is maintained by refreshed bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers, providing the communicative feedback and high-speed stability expected of an M-division product. While the exterior shows the light patina of a well-enjoyed driver's car, the drivetrain remains tight and the engine pulls strongly to its 8,000 RPM redline.",
